have intensified in recent years as media stocks have become market
favorites, and actual or prospective owners of newspapers and television properties have found it possible to capitalize increased audience
s.ize and adverti"iing revenues. into multiQlied values of the media franchises-and great wealth. 18 This has encouraged the entry of speculators and increased the pressure and temptation to focus more
intensively on profitability. Family owners have been increasingly divided between those wanting to take advantage of the new opportunities and those desiring a continuation of family control, and their splits

